openapi: 3.1.0
x-stoplight:
  id: 4am2q6x0h3c1j
info:
  title: Dataprius API v2
  version: '2.0'
  summary: This is the Dataprius API REST v2
  description: 'Dataprius offers a different way to work with files in the Cloud. It is designed for companies. It allows you to work with company files without synchronizing, without conflicts, with multiple Users connected at the same time.'
  contact:
    name: Dataprius Team
    url: 'https://dataprius.com/contacto.html'
    email: info@dataprius.com
  license:
    name: GPL-3.0 license
    url: 'https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html'
  termsOfService: 'https://dataprius.com/en/dataprius-legal-advice.html'
servers:
  - url: 'https://api.v2.dataprius.com'
paths:
  /oauth/token:
    get:
      summary: ''
      operationId: get-oauth-token
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  token_type:
                    type: string
                  created_at:
                    type: integer
                  access_token:
                    type: string
                  refresh_token:
                    type: string
                  expires_in:
                    type: integer
                x-examples:
                  Example 1:
                    token_type: bearer
                    created_at: 1687944522153
                    access_token: a492954ebad2187063fa5e09854bfd8222ad3fc3
                    refresh_token: 405bc5a2bcb5c026afed160085952ef37bb2d709
                    expires_in: 1687944529353
              examples:
                Example 1:
                  value:
                    token_type: bearer
                    created_at: 1687944522153
                    access_token: a492954ebad2187063fa5e09854bfd8222ad3fc3
                    refresh_token: 405bc5a2bcb5c026afed160085952ef37bb2d709
                    expires_in: 1687944529353
        '401':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/401-Invalid-Authorization'
        '429':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/429-Too-many-request'
      description: |-
        This is an Oauth2 basic authentication.

        To get an access token you will need the account’s Api keys. These are "clientId" and "clientSecret" credentials. You can get them from your Dataprius account configuration.

         If you do not have a Dataprius account, go to the website, download and install the <a href="https://dataprius.com/descargas">Free Version</a>. Once the application is installed. Go to the button in the lower left corner.

         Click Start -> Configuration -> API Keys

        There you can request API keys. There is a activation process. After that, you will see API Keys on the same window in Configuration.

        The Basic Authorization

        As is standard in basic access authentication, the header’s structure corresponds to Authorization Basic credentials, where credentials is the result of:

        Joining clientId and clientSecret by a single colon (:) Applying Base64 (URL safe mode) to the result.

        Basic Credentials is the result of base64(clientId + ":" + clientSecret)
      parameters:
        - schema:
            type: string
            default: Basic
            example: Basic MjUwZjBmYTVkN2VlYzNiN2QyZDE6ZWJhZTA2NDcxZTliMDA0YTYyNWJkM2M4NDU5ZGZmN2YwZjc2==
          in: header
          name: Authorization
          required: true
          description: Basic Authorization
